.row
  .span12
    %p 
      Weld is the reference implementation of 
      %a{:href=>"http://cdi-spec.org"}
        CDI: Contexts and Dependency Injection for the Java EE Platform
      which is the Java standard for dependency injection and contextual lifecycle management and one of the most important and popular parts of the Java EE platform.
    %p
      Weld is integrated into many Java EE application servers such as WildFly, JBoss Enterprise Application Platform, GlassFish, Oracle WebLogic and others. Weld can also be used in a Servlet-only environment (Tomcat, Jetty) or plain Java SE environment.
.row
  .span5
    %div
      %h1 Try Weld Today
      %div
        %p 
          To use Weld today, download the
          %a{:href=>"http://wildfly.org"}WildFly server
          (formelly JBoss AS) and add the following code to the 
          %em pom.xml
          file of your application:
        %pre.code
          = preserve do
            :escaped
              <dependency>
                 <groupId>javax.enterprise</groupId>
                 <artifactId>cdi-api</artifactId>
                 <version>1.1</version>
                 <scope>provided</scope>
              </dependency>
        %p
          For alternative ways of using Weld, see the
          %a{:href=>"/download"}download section
          or the
          %a{:href=>"http://docs.jboss.org/weld/reference/latest/en-US/html/environments.html"}reference documentation.
  .span3
    %div
      %h1 Weld Book
      %p The latest book on Weld is now available:
      %a{:href=>"http://www.packtpub.com/jboss-weld-cdi-for-java-platform/book"}
        %img{:src=>"images/book.jpg", :width=>"250", :height=>"307"}
  .span4
    %h1 News
    %ul.newsColumn
      - for post in site.posts[0,3]
        %li
          %h3
            %a{ :href=>post.url }#{post.title}
          - if (post.content.length > 0)
            %p
              %strong #{post.date.year}-#{post.date.month}-#{post.date.day}: #{post.author}
            %p= post.excerpt || summarize(html_to_text(post.content), 50)
            %a{:href=>post.url} Read more &raquo;
